    <div class="origin-box">
      <div class="origin-box-title">How the Belt Came to Be</div>
      <p>It started with Sam Johnson reaching into his golf bag and pulling out a camo canvas belt with a cannabis leaf buckle. The belt belonged to Frank Rennie. Sam looked at the group and suggested they play for it.</p>
      <p>Nobody said no. Nobody has said no since.</p>
      <p>The rules are simple: win The Belt Championship and you earn the right to sew a patch onto the belt — your initials and the year, stitched into the fabric permanently. The belt itself is a living record, worn and patched and carried forward into every future competition.</p>
      <p>What began at Boughton Golf Club in 2011 as a throwaway suggestion is now in its fifteenth year. The belt has seen six patches from Sam Johnson alone. It has never been more important.</p>
